faster code:
StringBuilder commandsBuf = "";
String sep = "";
for (String s : modArgs) {
  commandsBuf.append(sep).append(s);
  sep = " ";
}
String commands = commandsBuf.toString();

Doesn't make that much difference for this small array, but you should use the above pattern for creating a String from a bunch of concatenations with a separator.

For that matter, since you don't appear to USE the value of commands below for anything other than using it with .contains(), it would be much better if you just set a bunch of boolean variables indicating that things like "--imports" and "-i" were found and then test those booleans later. O(n) checks should be kept to a minimum.

